            . I am servant to Mr. 
               <persName id="t18220417-6-person99">
                  George 
                  Mott
               <interp inst="t18220417-6-person99" type="surname" value="Mott"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-6-person99" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-6-person99" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             of <placeName id="t18220417-6-crimeloc28">Essex-street, Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220417-6-crimeloc28" type="placeName" value="Essex-street, Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220417-6-crimeloc28" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220417-6-off26 t18220417-6-crimeloc28"></join>. On Monday, the 1st of April, about ten minutes past nine o'clock, I went out of the house, leaving the door ajar; I was returning in five minutes, and saw the prisoner come from the door - he went down to the bottom of the street. I followed him; he had something wrapped up in a handkerchief; he ran up Milford-lane; I overtook him at the top of the lane, and saw the shape of a cruet under his handkerchief; I said,</p>
               <p>"You have got my master's property." He said,</p>
               <p>"I have nothing of yours," and then threw it at me, handkerchief and all - I collared him, but he got away. I picked up the things, and then followed him, crying Stop thief! he was taken in about two minutes by Ross's. The glass of the cruet was broken - I produce it, I do not know the value of it. They are my master's.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. LAW. Q. Did you lose sight of him - A. In turning the corner. I am certain of him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220417-6-person100">
                  JOHN 
                  ROSS
               <interp inst="t18220417-6-person100" type="surname" value="ROSS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-6-person100" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-6-person100" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard the cry of Stop thief! and took the prisoner, who was running along Little Essex-street; the last witness came up in about a minute, with the stand in his hand.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 48.</p>
               <p>Of <rs id="t18220417-6-verdict29" type="verdictDescription">
